        "answer_count": 4,
        "title": "How to get back an object after performing .toString() on it?",
        "body": "<p>I have one class <strong>Data.java<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Data{\n   private String name;\n   private String age;\n   // getters and setters for the above fields\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In one of my method i performed <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  String newData = getData().toString();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But now i want the <strong>Data object<\/strong> back in its state instead of string object. so how to perform this in java.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 25801870,
        "tags": ["java"],
        "score": 1,
